    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_2_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_2",
      "description": "Available for acquisition is a 2004 BMW M3 (E46) featuring the high-revving S54 3.2L inline-six engine, renowned for its individual throttle bodies and 8,000 RPM redline. This specimen is equipped with the desirable Getrag 6-speed manual gearbox and a variable M differential lock for optimal torque distribution. Critical preventative maintenance has been addressed, including reinforcement of the rear subframe to maintain chassis integrity and a comprehensive VANOS system overhaul to ensure precise variable valve timing. The suspension geometry remains true, utilizing its original MacPherson strut front and multi-link rear configuration, though the bushings have been upgraded to polyurethane for crisper turn-in. While the exterior shows minor stone peppering consistent with spirited use, the powertrain exhibits excellent compression across all cylinders and linear power delivery. A recent valve clearance adjustment and Blackstone oil report confirm this M3 is mechanically primed for its next custodian.",
      "price": 33500.0,
      "reputation": 0.6,
      "quality": "poor",
      "quality_value": 0.1,
      "timestep_posted": 48
    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_9_listing_3",
